<worksheet xml:id="activity-tutorial-7">
  <title>Tutorial-7</title>
  <introduction>
                <p>
                    Following exercises are taken from Section 14.1 of the book <em>Abstract Algebra</em> by Dummit and Foote.
                </p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>X</m> be a nonempty subset of a field <m>K</m>, and let <m>K</m> be generated over a field <m>F</m> by <m>X</m>, i.e., <m>K=F(X)</m>. Show that any automorphism <m>\sigma</m> of <m>K</m> fixing <m>F</m> is uniquely determined by the action <m>\sigma</m> on <m>X</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>G\leq\Gal{K}{F}</m> be a subgroup of the Galois group of the extension <m>K/F</m>. Assume that <m>G</m> is generated by <m>\sigma_1,\sigma_2,\ldots,\sigma_n</m>. Show that the subfield <m>E/F</m> is fixed by <m>G</m> if and only if <m>E/F</m> is fixed by <m>\sigma_1,\sigma_2,\ldots,\sigma_n</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Determine all automorphisms of <m>\Q\left(\sqrt[4]{2}\right)</m> fixing <m>\Q\left(\sqrt{2}\right)</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Show that <m>\Aut{\R}{\Q}=\{\unit_\R\}</m> by proving the following.
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Show that any <m>\sigma\in\Aut{\R}{\Q}</m> takes squares to squares and a positive real number to a positive real number. Thus, show that if <m>a&lt;b</m> then, <m>\sigma a&lt;\sigma b</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Show that <m>\sigma\in\Aut{\R}{\Q}</m> is a continuous map by proving that the following.
                            <p>
                                For <m>m\in\N</m>, if <m>\tfrac{-1}{m}&lt;a-b&lt;\tfrac{1}{m}</m> then, <m>\tfrac{-1}{m}&lt;\sigma a-\sigma b&lt;\tfrac{1}{m}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Show that a continous real-valued map on <m>\R</m> which is identity on <m>\Q</m> is identity on <m>\R</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Show that the automorphisms of the rational function field <m>F(t)</m> fixing <m>F</m> are precisely <em>fractional linear transformations</em> detrmined by <m>t\mapsto at+b\big/ct+d</m>, where <m>a,b,c,d\in F</m> with <m>ad-bc\neq 0</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                Determine the fixed field of the automorphism of <m>F(t)</m> given by <me>\frac{f(t)}{g(t)}\mapsto \frac{f(1+t)}{g(1+t)}</me>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>K/F</m> be a field extension and <m>\varphi\colon K\to K'</m> an isomorphism of fields. Let <m>F'=\varphi(F)</m>. Show that the map <m>\Inn{\varphi}\colon\Aut{K}{F}\to\Aut{K'}{F'}</m> defined by <m>\sigma\mapsto\varphi\circ\sigma\circ\varphi^{-1}</m> is a group isomorphism.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>